HEADWORD: Porbeagle
<hw>Por"bea`gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A species of shark (<spn>Lamna cornubica</spn>), about eight feet
long, having a pointed nose and a crescent-shaped tail; -- called also
<altname>mackerel shark</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written <asp>also
probeagle</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Porcate</ent>⟦br⟧
